{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, joint sentiment/topic model (Lin and He 2009), Co-LDA (Wang 2010), sentence-LDA and aspect/sentiment unification model (Jo and Oh 2011), user-sentiment topic model (Zhao et al. 2012), Twitter opinion topic model (Lim and Buntine 2014), word-pair sentiment topic model (Xiong et al. 2018), and sentence segment LDA (Ozyurt and Akcayol 2021).",
    "The aim for the development of the algorithms is to improve on the performance of LDA that has been criticized for low performance in extracting topics in short texts.",
    "Generally, we observed that most publications with authors from non-computing background used LDA to extract topics for ABSA.",
    "This is not surprising as the approach is popular, and easy to use with available libraries in different programming languages.",
    "Overall, this result is consistent with the findings of Robledo and Zuluaga (2022) who highlighted sentiment analysis as one of the 4 research document clusters identified in their bibliometric analysis of TM studies."
  ],
